# PHASES

Dynamic phase description for TREF project.

## Current Phase: 7 - Polish & Documentation

Final polish, testing, and documentation.

### Remaining Tasks
- Screen reader support (live regions for status announcements)
- Manual testing (keyboard-only, mobile/touch)
- CONTRIBUTING.md for new developers
- UI/UX Build Guide on docs site

---

## Completed Phases

### Phase 6: CSS Architecture ✓
- Unified stylesheet (docs/css/tref-site.css)
- Removed all inline styles from HTML
- Dark mode via CSS custom properties
- Grouped selectors for maintainability

### Phase 5: Documentation Site ✓
- Live site at tref.lpmwfx.com
- Builder (no-code block creation)
- Guide (CLI, API, MCP)
- Examples (drag-drop, AI chat)
- Auto TREF block generation from markdown

### Phase 4: CLI & MCP ✓
- `tref publish` - create blocks
- `tref validate` - verify integrity
- `tref derive` - create child blocks
- `tref-mcp` - Claude Code integration

### Phase 3: Wrapper JS ✓
- TrefWrapper component (display, drag, copy, download)
- TrefReceiver component (drop zones)
- Accessibility (ARIA, keyboard, focus-visible)
- Touch support (tap-to-toggle, long-press)
- Theme support (light/dark via CSS variables)
- Published to npm as tref-block@0.1.0

### Phase 2: Publisher Core ✓
- Content-based ID generation (sha256)
- Canonical JSON serialization
- Publish, derive, validate functions
- File I/O (.tref files)

### Phase 1: Block Format Specification ✓
- Block schema (v, id, content, meta, origin, refs, parent)
- Reference types (url, archive, search, hash)
- ID format: sha256:<64 hex chars>
- Zod schemas with JSDoc types
- License-as-format philosophy
